nd the fight against terrorism, and analyzes the case of a Basque terrorist who tried to return to civilian life. Zulaika’s argument is powerful, inventive, and rich with insights and ideas that provide a new and sophisticated perspective on the War on Terror.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDiscourse analysis. 0aTerrorismxGovernment policy. 0aTerrorismxPrevention. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aterrorist, terror, violence, contemporary, modern, social problems, society, culture, cultural, history, historical, academic, scholarly, research, counterterrorism, future, realistic, prevention, war, logic, iraq, middle east, doctrine, intellectual, 9/11, psychology, psychological, in cold blood, orianna fallaci, jean genet, basque, civilian, catch 22.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022699415440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226994178423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226994178/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles